# neuxcfg

A production-ready Rust library for secure per-project configuration management.

## Quick Start

- Add dependency: `neuxcfg = "0.3.0"` (see Cargo.toml)
- Initialize global config store: See `src/lib.rs` – `Neuxcfg::init()`
- Add a project: `cfg.add_project("my_app")?` – src/lib.rs:add_project
- Read config: `cfg.get_project_config("my_app")?` – src/lib.rs:get_project_config
- Build the project: `cargo build` (standard Rust workflow)
- Join the community: [TODO: mailing list / IRC not specified in source]

## Essential Documentation

All users should be familiar with:

- Core API and usage: `src/lib.rs` (Neuxcfg struct documentation)
- Configuration structure: `src/types.rs` (GlobalConfig, ProjectConfig)
- Error handling: `src/error.rs` (NeuxcfgError enum)
- Validation rules: `src/validate.rs` (extra field restrictions)
- License: See COPYING or LICENSE (MIT – default from GlobalConfig)

